<item>
            <title>[LU-5870] New static analysis issues in llite</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5870</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After commit &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7069&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;b6e3612d845cf506e977f49aa85ddd1e709fd194&lt;/a&gt; the &apos;ln.ln_name&apos; and &apos;ln.ln_namelen&apos; might be used uninitialized in this function.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TRACEBACK:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;llite_lib.c:2823: &apos;ln.ln_namelen&apos; is declared.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;llite_lib.c:2837: Not entering loop, because ldata-&amp;gt;ld_lee!= ( (void* )0) is false&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;llite_lib.c:2850: &apos;ln.ln_namelen&apos; is used, but is uninitialized.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;llite_lib.c:2854: &apos;ln.ln_name&apos; is used, but is uninitialized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="27469">LU-5870</key>
